cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a new approach to integrating hardware-based data compression within the memory hierarchy, which falls under the domain of hardware architecture.
- cs.DC (Data Compression): The paper proposes a new compression algorithm and cache insertion policy, and discusses the benefits of compression in the memory hierarchy.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the impact of compression on performance and energy efficiency across the memory hierarchy, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper mentions the modest OS support required for the proposed approach, which falls under the domain of software engineering.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the adaptation of any compression algorithm to fit the requirements of the proposed main memory compression framework, which falls under the domain of programming languages.
